## Lessons

1. Use `npx shadcn@latest add [component]` instead of `npx shadcn-ui@latest add [component]` when installing Shadcn UI components.
2. In modern Next.js App Router, page params should be typed directly instead of wrapping them in a Promise.
   ```typescript
  interface PageProps {
  params: { id: string }
}

export default async function Page({ params }: PageProps) {
  const { id } = params
}
3. Use `const session = await auth()` instead of `const session = await getServerSession(authOptions)` for Next.js authentication. The new `auth()` function is the recommended way to get the session in Next.js Auth v5.
4.When importing useRouter from 'next/navigation', the component must be marked as a client component using the 'use client' directive at the top of the file, as this hook only works on the client side.

5.For guest checkout ecommerce systems, orders must not depend on a User model. Customer details such as name, email, phone, and shipping address must be stored directly on the Order model.

6.Carts in guest checkout systems should be session-based or localStorage-based rather than tied to a user account.

7.Orders must be created using payment webhooks (Paystack webhook) instead of relying on the success redirect page, to ensure orders are always recorded even if the user closes the browser.

8.Always generate readable order numbers (e.g., KM-20321) instead of relying only on random database IDs.

9.Prioritize mobile-first design, PWA support, and emerging-market payment methods (USSD, bank transfer, BNPL) for higher conversions. ✅

10.Integrate AI-powered search and recommendation engines (Perplexity, Algolia, or Gorse) to improve discovery and upselling. ✅

